Ok, if you are able to go this long without washing your hair , more power to you . The vast majority of us have to wash our hair often bc we produce a lot of oil . Before you start telling me that we can train to our scalp to produce less oil . No, most of us can’t and that’s on science . Plus , why are we torturing ourselves and force ourselves to do something that is not for us ? Whenever I don’t wash my hair , I feel miserable , gross, and my head hurts ! Whenever I wash my hair , I feel like a new person ! 
.
Plus there are so many things you can use now to protect our hair when washing it . Like using cowash from @asiamnaturally , apple cider vinegar rinse ( I prefer this from @dphue) I don’t make my own ACV rinse anymore bc it’s a hassle and it can be too acidic for more hair. 
.
Or use gentler shampoos with gentle surfactants . There are so many out in the market . My favorites at the moment are from @notyourmothers & @moroccanoil . 
. 
Last ,use a pre treatment or coconut oil . This helps protect your hair very well. 
.
Again , scalp health is important . Healthy scalp=Healthy hair . Our hair is dead , we can protect it with products and lifestyle habits , but eventually it’ll get some damage . Enjoy and have fun with your hair .
.
Again , if you prefer going many days without washing your hair , this is not against you . This is specifically for those that follow people telling them that they can train their hair but ended up feeling miserable with dirty oily hair and irritated scalp . You don’t have to be miserable , go and wash your hair ! 
.
.
#haircaretips #healthyhairjourney #haircare 
.
.

Do you use a heat protectant? It’s important to use a good heat protectant when you use hot tools .Even if it is a Dyson. 
.
These are three heat protectants I like currently.
@pureology Color Fanatic Multi-Tasking Leave-In Spray is an oldie but a goodie . Contains Camelina Oi,Coconut Oil, and Olive Oil. This is specifically for colored hair , but I think this works for all hair . It’s super lightweight and smells lovely . It also protects hair from UV ray.
.
@kerastase_official Serum Chroma Thermique Hair Serum. It’s a new product from Kerastase. It’s specifically for colored hair , but can work for all hair . This is my new obsession . It’s lightweight , smells amazing , and makes my hair soft. It contains lactic acid to exfoliate the hair surface , and Centella Asiatica soothes and nourishes hair . It doesn’t have UV protectant .
.
@kenraprofessional Platinum Blow-Dry Spray . If you are someone who likes to blow dry Your hair , get this . It will cut your blow dry time in half! Less heat time =healthier hair . Contains Argan and jojoba oils . It leaves my hair bouncy and shiny. I’m not sure if this is a UV protectant or not bc I dont see the claim anywhere . 
.
.
.
.

Original video @sofiyaguliyeva 
.
#haircaretips #kerastaseofficial #pureology #hairreels #healthyhaircare

New Products @ultabeauty 
.
I went and got several new products at Ultabeauty to try out.
.
@tula Bright Start Vitamin C Moisturizer is moisturizing without being too heavy . It has vitamin C and tranexamic acid . It has a light citrusy scent  to me. It’s supposed to brighten skin and help with reducing hyperpigmentation. I haven’t tried it long enough to say that it actually help with that . But I like how lightweight and moisturizing as well . 
.
@fentybeauty is at Ulta Beauty now ! I  got excited and got several of her products . 
The Eaze Drop Blurring Skin Tint is lovely. Lightweight , buildable , flawless finish . If you are into the glowing skin tint look, this is not for you . I find this to be on the matte side .
.
The semi matte lipstick shade balling babe is so pretty. Good formula , lightweight , pigmented , and lasts about 3-4 hours . I also like the lipstick case ! 
.
I have short and super straight lashes , and I always like to try new mascara. The new @lancomeofficial Idole Lash Mascara looks pretty . It Adds length and a little bit of volume for me . 
.

This is an ad on Tiktok . But I like the products and want to share on here too .❤️

Sunscreen isn’t just for sunny days ,it’s the gentle protection your skincare needs every day. Think of it as the final step that helps all your other products shine.

Here are three new sunscreens I’ve been using lately:

✨ @Glow Recipe Watermelon Glow Dew Shield SPF 30 – This is their new and improved version, and it feels super smooth on the skin. It leaves my skin looking glowy and fresh. It’s a chemical sunscreen that doubles as a great primer and layers well over makeup when reapplying.

💧 @First Aid Beauty Hydrating Sunscreen Milk with Colloidal Oatmeal Broad Spectrum SPF 45 – Very light and easy to blend into the skin. It’s a no-frills, dependable chemical sunscreen that’s hydrating and works well for reapplication, though it can shift makeup slightly.

🌿 Beekman 1802 Solar Milk Clear SPF 50 Sunscreen Gel – Lightweight and hydrating, this chemical sunscreen applies nicely under makeup. However, it feels a bit too oily for reapplication, and the pump packaging needs improvement ,it takes some effort to get the product out.
.
.
#sunscreens #skincaretips #antiaging #glowrecipe

Makeup meets skincare ✨
The new @glowrecipe Glass Balms are a great addition to their makeup line. Infused with hyaluronic acid microspheres and glycerin, they’re lightweight yet super glossy, and they smell like watermelon 🍉
I love pairing them with the Watermelon Glow Niacinamide Dewy Flush for that extra dewy glow.
